{"title_page": "Ho\u00e0ng Sa District", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Ho\u00e0ng Sa District \n|settlement_type        = [[District (Vietnam)|District (Island)]]\n|official_name          = Ho\u00e0ng Sa Island District\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = Huy\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea3o Ho\u00e0ng Sa\n|nickname               = \n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|image_map1             = \n|mapsize1               = \n|map_caption1           =\n|pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = {{flag|Vietnam}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Vietnam|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[South Central Coast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Provinces of Vietnam|Province]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Da Nang]]\n|seat_type              =\n|seat                   = \n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           = People's Committee Chairman\n|leader_name            = V\u00f5 C\u00f4ng Ch\u00e1nh<ref name=vccchanh />\n|leader_title1          = Headquarters\n|leader_name1           = 132 Y\u00ean B\u00e1i St., [[H\u1ea3i Ch\u00e2u District|H\u1ea3i Ch\u00e2u District]], Da Nang\n|established_title      =  \n|established_date       = \n|area_magnitude         = \n|unit_pref              =Imperial<!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n|area_footnotes         = \n|area_total_km2         = 305 \n|area_land_km2          = \n|area_water_km2         = \n|area_total_sq_mi       = \n|area_land_sq_mi        = \n|area_water_sq_mi       = \n|area_water_percent     = \n|area_urban_km2         = \n|area_urban_sq_mi       = \n|area_metro_km2         = \n|area_metro_sq_mi       = \n|population_as_of       =\n|population_footnotes   = \n|population_note        = \n|population_total       =\n|population_density_km2 = \n|population_density_sq_mi = \n|population_metro       =\n|population_density_metro_km2 =\n|population_density_metro_sq_mi =\n|population_urban       = \n|population_density_urban_km2 =\n|population_density_urban_mi2 =\n| timezone = Indochina Time\n| utc_offset = +7\n|latd=|latm=|lats=|latNS=\n|longd=|longm=|longs= |longEW=\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m              = \n|elevation_ft           = \n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              = \n|website                = {{URL|http://hoangsa.danang.gov.vn/index.php}}\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Ho\u00e0ng Sa''' is an island [[Districts of Vietnam|district]] of [[Da Nang]] in the [[South Central Coast]] region of Vietnam.<ref>{{in lang|vi}}{{cite web|url=http://www.vietlaw.gov.vn/LAWNET/docView.do?docid=4531|title=Ngh\u1ecb \u0111\u1ecbnh c\u1ee7a Ch\u00ednh ph\u1ee7 07-CP ng\u00e0y 23 th\u00e1ng 01 n\u0103m 1997 v\u1ec1 vi\u1ec7c th\u00e0nh l\u1eadp \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ecb h\u00e0nh ch\u00ednh tr\u1ef1c thu\u1ed9c th\u00e0nh ph\u1ed1 \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng|accessdate=2012-08-28}}</ref> It covers an area of {{convert|305|km2|abbr=on}} of the [[Paracel Islands]], including these main features: Pattle Island, North Reef, Robert Island, Discovery Reef, Passu Keah, [[Triton Island]], [[Tree Island, South China Sea|Tree Island]], North Island, Middle Island, South Island, [[Woody Island, South China Sea|Woody Island]], Lincoln Island, Duncan Island, [[Bombay Reef]], Observation Bank, West Sand, Vuladdore Reef and Pyramid Rock.<ref>{{in lang|vi}}{{cite web|url=http://www.danangcity.gov.vn/portal/page/portal/danang/chinhquyen/gioi_thieu/don_vi_hanh_chinh?p_pers_id=&p_folder_id=6904276&p_main_news_id=8981394&p_year_sel=|publisher=Da Nang City|title=Huy\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea3o Ho\u00e0ng Sa [Hoang Sa District]|accessdate=2012-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904011606/http://www.danangcity.gov.vn/portal/page/portal/danang/chinhquyen/gioi_thieu/don_vi_hanh_chinh?p_pers_id=&p_folder_id=6904276&p_main_news_id=8981394&p_year_sel=|archive-date=4 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2009, Vietnam appointed an official, \u0110\u1eb7ng C\u00f4ng Ng\u1eef, to be the first<ref name=vccchanh>{{in lang|vi}}{{cite web|url=http://vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/thoi-su/da-nang-co-tan-chu-tich-huyen-dao-hoang-sa-2986291.html|publisher=VnExpress|title=\n\u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng c\u00f3 t\u00e2n ch\u1ee7 t\u1ecbch huy\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea3o Ho\u00e0ng Sa [Danang has new chairman of Hoang Sa District]|date=2014-05-05|accessdate=2014-07-14}}</ref> chairman of Ho\u00e0ng Sa District.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cmLP3UXJyvoC&pg=PA189&lpg=PA189&dq=the+establishment+of+%22hoang+sa+district%22&source=bl&ots=dJ34tL60FG&sig=OponiwnWh2oo-ssVL36un1meHaM&hl=en#v=onepage&q&f=false|author=Zhiqun Zhu|title=China's New Diplomacy: Rationale, Strategies and Significance|page=189|ISBN=9781409401674|accessdate=2012-08-28}}</ref><ref name=monre>{{cite web|url=http://www.monre.gov.vn/v35/default.aspx?tabid=675&CateID=80&ID=63594&Code=LUYVP63594|title=Hoang Sa Island district to have new chairman|publisher=Ministry of Natural Resources and Environment of Vietnam|accessdate=2012-08-28|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121224225913/http://www.monre.gov.vn/v35/default.aspx?tabid=675&CateID=80&ID=63594&Code=LUYVP63594|archivedate=24 December 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The incumbent is V\u00f5 C\u00f4ng Ch\u00e1nh, who was appointed on May 5, 2014.<ref name=vccchanh /> Vietnam does not control any of the islands it claims and the entire [[Paracel Islands]] is under the administration of the [[People's Republic of China]] as part of [[Sansha]] prefecture.\n\nVietnam established Ho\u00e0ng Sa district in 1982 as part of [[Qu\u1ea3ng Nam-Da Nang]] province.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vietnam.vn/the-hoang-sa-paracel-and-truong-sa-spratly-archipelagoes-and-international-law-1988-c1070n20120102121508750.htm |title=The Hoang Sa (Paracel) and Truong Sa (Spratly) archipelagoes and international law 1988 |publisher=Authority of Foreign Information Service of Vietnam |accessdate=2012-08-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313233455/http://www.vietnam.vn/the-hoang-sa-paracel-and-truong-sa-spratly-archipelagoes-and-international-law-1988-c1070n20120102121508750.htm |archivedate=13 March 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Since Qu\u1ea3ng Nam and Da Nang were split in November 1996, the island district has belonged to Da Nang.<ref name=monre/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Battle of the Paracel Islands]]\n*[[Paracel Islands]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Districts of South Central Coast}}\n\n{{coord|16|32|05|N|111|36|30|E|type:city_source:kolossus-viwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hoa Vang District}}\n[[Category:Districts of Da Nang]]\n[[Category:Paracel Islands]]\n\n{{DaNang-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Ho\u00e0ng Sa District \n|settlement_type        = [[District (Vietnam)|District (Island)]]\n|official_name          = Ho\u00e0ng Sa Island District\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = Huy\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea3o Ho\u00e0ng Sa\n|nickname               = \n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map        